{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The gutter view displays line numbers that match the text view’s line indexes."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This view is used as a scroll view’s ruler view. It sits on top of the text view so text scrolls underneath the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"gutter if line wrapping is disabled.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"text":"MainActor","kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GutterView","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the gutter needs more space (when the number of digits in the numbers increases eg. adding a line after line 99),"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it will notify it’s delegate via the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GutterViewDelegate\/gutterViewWidthDidUpdate(newWidth:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method. In"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"SourceEditor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", this notifies the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/codeeditsourceeditor.CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/TextViewController","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", which in turn updates the textview’s edge insets"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to adjust for the new leading inset."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This view also listens for selection updates, and draws a selected background on selected lines to keep the illusion","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that the gutter’s line numbers are inline with the line itself.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The gutter view has insets of it’s own that are relative to the widest line index. By default, these insets are 20px"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"leading, and 12px trailing. However, this view also has a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GutterView\/backgroundEdgeInsets"},{"text":" property, that pads","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the rect that has a background drawn. This allows the text to be scrolled under the gutter view for 8px before being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overlapped by the gutter. It should help the textview keep the cursor visible if the user types while the cursor is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"off the leading edge of the editor."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/codeeditsourceeditor.CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/GutterView"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Text View","identifiers":["doc:\/\/codeeditsourceeditor.CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/SourceEditorView","doc:\/\/codeeditsourceeditor.CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/SourceEditor","doc:\/\/codeeditsourceeditor.CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/SourceEditorConfiguration","doc:\/\/codeeditsourceeditor.CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/SourceEditorState","doc:\/\/codeeditsourceeditor.CodeEditSourceEditor\/documentation\/CodeEditSourceEditor\/TextViewController"],"anchor":"Text-View"}],"metadata":{"externalID":"c:@M@CodeEditSourceEditor@objc(cs)GutterView","symbolKind":"class","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GutterView","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"GutterView","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"CodeEditSourceEditor"}],"roleHeading":"Class","title":"GutterView","role":"symbol"},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":